  "text": "where the inflow through the neck artery q b,na , outflow through the neck vein q b,nv , and CSF absorption q b;f 2 are the only net effects on the volumes that comprise the intracranial volume V b,ic in Eq. [CITATION_1] . The remaining unknown is the intracranial compliance C b,ic . In [CITATION_2] , the intracranial compliance is defined as inversely proportional to the intracranial pressure. Substituting this inverse proportionality into Eq. (36), however, results in a constant intracranial volume, which implies zero intracranial compliance. Given this inconsistency, we opted instead to use the Windkessel compliance of Eq. (7) with s = b and j = ic. Rearranging Eq. (7) illustrates that larger values of b b,ic result in a compliance expression that is nearly equivalent to the one in [CITATION_3] but the algebraic cancelation of P b,ic is avoided",
